04:01.770 --> 04:03.437
Hey, I use Febreze.

04:03.521 --> 04:05.106
Yes, you do.

04:05.189 --> 04:06.816
By the way, it's not a body spray.

04:06.900 --> 04:07.942
Oh.

04:09.736 --> 04:11.487
Yeah, and Copenhagen
ain't a breath mint,

04:11.570 --> 04:12.822
but when you're in a jam,
you're in a jam.

04:12.906 --> 04:13.948
[laughs]

04:14.032 --> 04:15.408
[sighs] All right.

04:15.491 --> 04:17.285
- All right.
- Okay.

04:17.368 --> 04:18.411
Where do you think we are?

04:19.745 --> 04:21.579
- Hmm.
- Oh, this is awesome.

04:21.664 --> 04:23.624
- You're never gonna get it.
- Laundromat?

04:23.707 --> 04:24.918
Are you fucking kidding me?

04:25.001 --> 04:26.252
[laughing]

04:26.335 --> 04:27.378
Did you peek?

04:27.461 --> 04:28.504
Of course I peeked.

04:28.587 --> 04:30.714
I'm a woman in a blindfold
being put into a truck.

04:30.799 --> 04:32.050
[Colt chuckles]

04:32.884 --> 04:34.844
Well, it ain't just a Laundromat.

04:34.928 --> 04:36.595
This is a special place
from our history.

04:38.014 --> 04:41.559
Okay, a candlelit picnic in a Laundromat.

04:41.642 --> 04:43.812
I'm just gonna say this,
and I'm not mad...

04:44.312 --> 04:47.481
but I think this might be an inside joke
between you and a different girl.

04:48.024 --> 04:50.151
No, this is where we had our first date.

04:50.234 --> 04:52.821
No, it was at Rick's Arcade City.

04:53.571 --> 04:55.239
This is Rick's!

04:55.323 --> 04:56.783
Well, I mean, at least, it was.

04:56.866 --> 04:59.493
Rick had to sell it after that
incident with the Cub Scouts.

05:02.496 --> 05:04.165
Oh, my God!

05:04.248 --> 05:06.459
Yes, I forgot that they redid it.

05:06.542 --> 05:08.294
- [chuckles] Yeah.
- [sighs]

05:08.377 --> 05:10.088
- We played skee ball...
- Yeah.

05:10.171 --> 05:12.340
For hours until we'd get enough tickets

05:12.423 --> 05:15.093
to get one of those
crazy giant sunglasses.

05:15.176 --> 05:18.179
All right, you mean, uh... these?

05:18.262 --> 05:19.555
[gasps]

05:19.638 --> 05:21.224
- [chuckles]
- How did you get those?

05:21.307 --> 05:23.434
I bought 'em at the 99 cent store.

05:23.517 --> 05:24.768
[laughs] Oh, my God!

05:24.853 --> 05:27.333
Yeah, it turns out we could've
gone there all along. [Chuckles]

05:28.189 --> 05:31.150
Hey, uh, remember outside,
the go-kart track they had?

05:31.234 --> 05:34.445
Yeah, you put me into the wall
on turn three and I busted my lip.

05:35.113 --> 05:37.656
[chuckles] Whatever. Rubbin's Racin'.

05:38.950 --> 05:40.534
Remember you come around that last lap

05:40.618 --> 05:42.954
and passed me with a mouthful of blood?

05:44.580 --> 05:46.832
That's when I knew we were meant to be.

05:46.916 --> 05:48.251
[chuckles]

05:50.586 --> 05:52.005
How did you arrange all this?

05:52.964 --> 05:55.758
[smacks lips] Remember
Cooper Wynn, my tight end?

05:56.592 --> 05:58.970
Wait, was he the guy that
peed in the Gatorade bucket

05:59.053 --> 06:01.055
before dumping it on the coach's head?

06:02.932 --> 06:04.183
No, that was me.

06:05.851 --> 06:07.353
No, Cooper's the one I framed for it.

06:07.436 --> 06:08.729
[chuckles]

06:08.812 --> 06:10.398
He bought this place
with the money he got

06:10.481 --> 06:12.483
from the settlement
after the coach hit him.

06:14.193 --> 06:15.904
And he helped me set all this up.

06:17.030 --> 06:20.408
All right, Colt. This might be
the fumes from the bleach talking, but...

06:21.742 --> 06:22.785
this is so sweet.

06:25.454 --> 06:26.664
[Colt chuckles]

06:29.375 --> 06:31.460
Hmm, someone's excited.

06:31.544 --> 06:33.504
Oh... no. Just a roll of quarters.

06:33.587 --> 06:34.713
[chuckles]

06:36.049 --> 06:37.675
[smacks lips] You know...

06:37.758 --> 06:40.636
in case we get naked
and have to do some laundry.

06:40.719 --> 06:42.013
[chuckling]

06:52.315 --> 06:53.357
[Maggie sighs]

06:54.400 --> 06:55.693
- Hey, Rooster.
- Hey, Ma.

06:55.776 --> 06:58.446
What's the strongest thing
you got in this place?

06:58.529 --> 07:00.823
Oh, probably the oven cleaner.

07:03.451 --> 07:05.744
Great. Add some orange juice
and some grenadine.

07:05.828 --> 07:07.455
We'll call it a "Rooster sunrise."

07:08.957 --> 07:10.208
Make it two.

07:12.668 --> 07:14.545
All right, what'd your dad do?

07:14.628 --> 07:17.298
Well, he could have visited more.

07:18.716 --> 07:20.134
Not you, Hank.

07:20.759 --> 07:22.845
So, is the insemination not going well?

07:22.929 --> 07:24.763
Again, not you, Hank.

07:26.140 --> 07:27.350
I wouldn't know.

07:27.433 --> 07:29.593
He took the job away from us.
Decided to do it himself.

07:30.019 --> 07:31.895
- What? Why?
- Why?

07:31.980 --> 07:33.772
'Cause he thinks he's
the best at everything.

07:33.856 --> 07:35.816
It's like why he grabs the communion
out of the priest's hands.

07:35.899 --> 07:37.610
He's like, "No, no. I got this."

07:39.820 --> 07:43.157
Son of a bitch. I thought for
once he'd actually listen to me.

07:43.824 --> 07:45.952
Only way he's gonna listen
to you is if you said,

07:46.035 --> 07:47.661
"Ronald Reagan told me

07:47.745 --> 07:49.705
John Wayne said,
'Give them boys a shot.'"

07:52.250 --> 07:55.753
I can't believe it. It's shit like this
that's making me divorce your father.

07:55.836 --> 07:58.256
Yeah, trust me, I'm done with him, too.

07:58.339 --> 07:59.798
Wish there was a way
to get the fuck out of there.

07:59.882 --> 08:01.722
I just don't know
how or where to go, you know?

08:02.426 --> 08:05.346
It's like that Halloween
I woke up naked in a corn maze.

08:07.223 --> 08:09.683
I know you're frustrated,
but you're gonna figure something out.

08:09.767 --> 08:12.353
The Rooster I know
is ambitious and driven.

08:12.436 --> 08:15.189
You used to make and sell
your own beef jerky.

08:15.273 --> 08:16.524
Yeah. [Chuckles]

08:16.607 --> 08:18.776
That's what kept me alive
in that corn maze.

08:19.860 --> 08:22.071
You used to grow and sell your own weed.

08:22.155 --> 08:23.197
[chuckles]

08:23.281 --> 08:25.081
That's how I ended up naked
in that corn maze.

08:27.660 --> 08:28.911
The point is...

08:29.620 --> 08:31.039
you can't give up on yourself.

08:31.122 --> 08:33.124
There's a whole world of opportunities.

08:33.207 --> 08:34.917
Yeah, you're probably right.

08:35.001 --> 08:36.960
Hey, maybe I can come down
here and work with you?

08:37.044 --> 08:39.922
Oh, honey, I could never trust
you around all this alcohol.

08:43.759 --> 08:45.011
[Colt sighs]

08:46.554 --> 08:48.972
- [Colt chuckles]
- Mmm.

08:49.057 --> 08:50.724
Hmm, is it just me...

08:51.725 --> 08:54.020
or are we better at this than we
were in high school? [Chuckles]

08:54.103 --> 08:56.397
- [chuckles] Well, I know you are.
- Oh.

08:56.480 --> 08:59.108
- I've always been awesome.
- [chuckles]

08:59.692 --> 09:01.402
- Truth.
- Hmm.

09:02.820 --> 09:03.862
[kisses]

09:03.946 --> 09:05.781
Did you know we'd get back together?

09:06.282 --> 09:08.367
- Never had a doubt.
- Aw.

09:08.451 --> 09:11.370
What about you?
Think we'd get back together?

09:11.454 --> 09:12.538
No.

09:12.621 --> 09:14.998
And I promised, like,
six friends that I never would.

09:15.083 --> 09:16.250
[Colt chuckles]

09:16.334 --> 09:17.793
Fuck them bitches.

09:19.087 --> 09:20.421
[both chuckle]

09:20.504 --> 09:23.006
- I haven't even told them yet.
- Mmm.

09:29.930 --> 09:31.932
- You know, it's still early.
- Hmm.

09:32.015 --> 09:33.726
The rodeo in town. You wanna go?

09:33.809 --> 09:35.561
I'm not really a big fan.

09:35.644 --> 09:37.938
- What? Are you kidding?
- Mmm.

09:38.021 --> 09:40.023
They have beer, bulls, and burgers.

09:40.108 --> 09:42.360
Little kids chasing around greased pigs.

09:42.443 --> 09:44.528
You don't like that,
you don't like America.

09:45.279 --> 09:46.947
It's just the way they treat the animals.

09:47.906 --> 09:48.949
What?

09:49.032 --> 09:51.660
Roping 'em, and tying
'em up and riding 'em?

09:51.744 --> 09:53.496
Well, that's my plan for the weekend.

09:53.579 --> 09:55.081
[both chuckle]

09:56.957 --> 09:58.334
[Colt] Mmm.

09:58.417 --> 10:01.254
All right... you want to see a movie?

10:01.337 --> 10:03.589
- Yeah. Yeah, sure.
- Great.

10:03.672 --> 10:06.175
Johnny Knoxville's got this new one out.

10:06.259 --> 10:08.219
[laughs] It looks so stupid.

10:08.302 --> 10:09.762
I can't wait to see it.

10:10.929 --> 10:13.224
Mmm, okay. Yeah, maybe.

10:13.307 --> 10:17.145
Or Alfonso CuarÃ³n made a movie
about how there's no more music.

10:17.228 --> 10:19.480
Mmm, that sounds good.

10:19.563 --> 10:22.024
Does this Alfonso guy
shit in a tuba or something?

10:23.192 --> 10:24.818
No. No.

10:24.902 --> 10:28.322
