<i>A Tale of Two Cities.</i>

15:36.046 --> 15:38.340
There... perfect.

15:38.424 --> 15:39.842
Here you go. [Clears throat]

15:40.551 --> 15:42.511
Oh, that...

15:42.594 --> 15:45.055
Maybe we should start with <i>A
Tale of One City.</i> [chuckles]

15:47.182 --> 15:48.976
Colt, seriously,
you don't have to do this.

15:50.310 --> 15:51.895
- It'll be fun.
- [chuckles]

15:52.813 --> 15:54.565
- Oh.
- [chuckles] Yeah.

15:54.648 --> 15:57.443
- All right, here we go.
- All right, here we go.

15:57.526 --> 15:59.695
[reading] "To my dear wife, Catherine."

15:59.778 --> 16:01.989
- [scoffs] That was easy.
- [both chuckle]

16:02.072 --> 16:03.824
See? It's fun.

16:03.907 --> 16:05.951
All right, next. [Sighs]

16:07.077 --> 16:11.457
"It was the best of times,
it was the worst of times."

16:13.584 --> 16:15.586
What the fuck does that mean?

16:22.092 --> 16:24.011
Oh, shit, is there a spider?

16:24.636 --> 16:25.554
What?

16:25.638 --> 16:27.014
No.

16:27.097 --> 16:28.181
Why you holding that book?

16:28.932 --> 16:30.058
I'm reading it.

16:31.268 --> 16:32.352
Why? Is the TV broke?

16:33.479 --> 16:35.523
No, man, I love to read.

16:35.606 --> 16:36.690
Since when?

16:36.774 --> 16:39.614
You have a meltdown if the menu
doesn't have pictures of the food on it.

16:39.902 --> 16:42.738
[sighing] I'm doing it for Abby.

16:42.821 --> 16:45.407
We're both reading it.
And I gotta tell you, it sucks.

16:45.491 --> 16:46.700
At least for me.

16:46.784 --> 16:48.786
She's sitting there,
smiling, flipping pages,

16:48.869 --> 16:50.871
making notes, which I totally don't get.

16:50.954 --> 16:53.666
Unless she's writing a suicide note
'cause she's forced to read this shit.

16:53.749 --> 16:55.333
[chuckles]

16:55.417 --> 16:56.794
Meanwhile, all I'm doing
is sitting there thinking,

16:56.877 --> 16:59.638
"I wonder if this guy got made fun of
'cause his last name's Dickens."

17:00.839 --> 17:03.258
"Hey, Charles, what'd you
stick your Dick-ins?"

17:03.341 --> 17:04.885
[chuckles] That's a good one.

17:04.968 --> 17:07.470
Hey, you know how they say, uh,
"You got your face in a book?"

17:07.555 --> 17:09.138
Well, you got a Dick-ins your face.

17:11.559 --> 17:13.476
- So then, why are you reading it?
- Oh.

17:13.560 --> 17:15.186
- Abby loves to read.
- Mmm.

17:15.270 --> 17:16.396
I thought it was something
we could do together.

17:16.479 --> 17:18.106
You know she don't even own a TV?

17:19.398 --> 17:20.733
That is fucked up.

17:22.528 --> 17:24.696
I don't know. It got me
to thinking, like...

17:24.780 --> 17:26.699
how much do we actually have in common?

17:26.781 --> 17:28.951
I mean, we can't
just have sex all the time.

17:29.034 --> 17:31.704
What the hell's wrong with you?
That book put that in your head?

17:34.748 --> 17:35.791
Yeah.

17:37.042 --> 17:38.126
Howdy, boys.

17:38.877 --> 17:40.588
- Hey, Dale. What's the good word?
- Hey, Dale.

17:40.671 --> 17:43.465
I've been regular
for three days straight.

17:45.342 --> 17:48.804
Okay, I meant more of, like,
"Why are you here?" But that's cool, too.

17:48.887 --> 17:51.765
Well, I dropped in
to check on that bunch of heifers,

17:51.849 --> 17:54.517
and your dad made
five out of eight pregnant.

17:55.352 --> 17:57.187
- Well, good for you.
- Awesome.

17:57.270 --> 17:59.648
It's not about me, it's about all of us.

17:59.732 --> 18:00.858
About the ranch.

18:00.941 --> 18:02.985
Yeah, okay. Whatever you say.

18:03.068 --> 18:05.028
Well, I'm gonna swing by Mary's
on the way to the bar.

18:05.112 --> 18:06.154
See you guys later.

18:06.238 --> 18:07.865
I'm going to Abby's. See you, Dale.

18:07.948 --> 18:09.950
Dale, good luck on day four.

18:13.871 --> 18:15.706
What the hell's wrong with them?

18:15.789 --> 18:19.292
They're mad 'cause I was right
about taking this job away from them.

18:20.377 --> 18:22.295
They don't see the bigger picture.

18:23.631 --> 18:25.716
You got time to stay for a whiskey?

18:25.799 --> 18:26.925
No, can't do it.

18:27.009 --> 18:29.219
Charlene and I got a movie night.

18:29.302 --> 18:30.846
Which reminds me...

18:32.180 --> 18:35.433
- What are you doing?
- Oh, I'm turning these hearing aids down.

18:36.018 --> 18:38.687
Charlene always picks them
romantic comedies.

18:38.771 --> 18:42.107
This way, I can pretend the
characters are talking about fishing.

18:47.780 --> 18:48.864
[door closes]

18:48.947 --> 18:50.866
Colt, what are you doing?

18:50.949 --> 18:53.994
[chuckles] Hey, surprise!
I got you a TV.

18:54.077 --> 18:56.288
Now we can binge watch
<i>Ice Road Truckers.</i>

18:56.371 --> 18:57.706
What?

18:57.790 --> 19:00.583
Oh, it's from the producers of <i>Ax
Men</i> and <i>Deadliest Catch.</i>

19:01.418 --> 19:04.963
I mean, I know what all those
words mean separately, but...

19:05.588 --> 19:06.757
Well, I just... I figured,

19:06.840 --> 19:10.343
if we were reading books together,
something you like to do...

19:10.427 --> 19:12.763
we could do something I like to do.
Hence, the TV.

19:12.846 --> 19:13.972
- Hence?
- Yeah.

19:14.056 --> 19:16.350
I read it in that
<i>Tale of a Couple Cities.</i>

19:17.643 --> 19:19.853
Hence, the use of "hence." [chuckles]

19:20.437 --> 19:21.479
Colt...

19:22.731 --> 19:24.107
'Twas a bad idea?

19:25.859 --> 19:28.737
I... I wanna do things with you, too.
But...

19:30.113 --> 19:31.823
I really don't want a TV.

19:31.907 --> 19:32.950
Oh.

19:34.117 --> 19:36.119
Okay. [Stammers]

19:37.037 --> 19:38.121
What are we gonna do?

19:39.164 --> 19:43.418
'Cause you don't wanna go to the rodeo,
and we can't agree on a movie.

19:43.501 --> 19:44.753
Now, I tried to read that book,

19:44.837 --> 19:47.005
and I gotta tell you,
it 'twas the worst of times.

19:49.132 --> 19:50.759
I never asked you to read it.

19:50.843 --> 19:52.427
I mean, where is this coming from?

19:52.928 --> 19:54.262
I don't know. Uh...

19:55.180 --> 19:57.099
You know,
I'm a guy who gets off of work,

19:57.182 --> 19:59.434
and comes home,
and cracks a beer and watches TV.

19:59.517 --> 20:00.518
Yeah.

20:00.602 --> 20:02.896
Yeah, and you're a teacher,
who gets off of work,

20:02.980 --> 20:05.148
and has a glass of white wine
and reads Dickens.

20:05.941 --> 20:08.318
And see, and the fact that you
don't laugh when I say "Dick-ins"

20:08.401 --> 20:10.112
just means we're total opposites.

20:10.988 --> 20:13.824
Oh, please. I mean, I've heard
every Dickens joke there is.

20:13.907 --> 20:16.869
Wait until we get to Longfellow,
or <i>Moby Dick.</i>

20:18.829 --> 20:20.330
It's about a giant sperm whale.

20:20.413 --> 20:22.457
All right, now you're
just fucking with me.

20:24.376 --> 20:26.962
Look, I'm just...
I'm afraid that me being me

20:27.045 --> 20:28.421
ain't gonna mix with you being you,

20:28.505 --> 20:30.090
and then you're just
gonna get bored of me.

20:30.173 --> 20:31.800
Why would I get bored with you?

20:31.884 --> 20:34.762
'Cause we got nothing in common.
Except for great sex.

20:34.845 --> 20:36.889
Oh, Colt, that is not true.

20:36.972 --> 20:39.767
I mean, I'm interested
in more than just sex with you.

20:40.558 --> 20:42.227
[chuckles] I mean, you make me laugh.

20:43.020 --> 20:44.187
You're spontaneous.

20:44.271 --> 20:46.732
I mean, that Laundromat thing
was so sweet.

20:46.815 --> 20:48.984
And no one's ever done
anything like that for me.

20:49.067 --> 20:51.694
So we have different interests.

20:51.779 --> 20:53.030
I mean, who cares?

20:53.947 --> 20:56.574
We're a dichotomy, but we're symbiotic.

20:57.409 --> 21:00.412
Okay, them words, I don't even know
what they mean separately. [Chuckles]

21:02.289 --> 21:03.623
Point is, it's okay.

21:03.706 --> 21:06.001
I mean, I can teach you big words

21:06.084 --> 21:07.085
- and...
- [chuckles]

21:07.169 --> 21:09.504
You can teach me who the weak side
linebacker is for the Broncos.

21:09.587 --> 21:11.214
[chuckles] I'm kidding,
it's DeMarcus Ware,

21:11.298 --> 21:12.632
but that's not the point.

21:14.176 --> 21:16.219
You don't have to put
so much pressure on yourself.

21:16.303 --> 21:19.347
I don't care if you ever read a book
for the rest of your life.

21:20.682 --> 21:23.268
That is the greatest gift
you could ever possibly give me.

21:23.351 --> 21:24.519
[chuckles]

21:25.228 --> 21:28.106
I just don't want you to blow up
your whole life to be with me,

21:28.190 --> 21:32.027
and then realize you made, like, a...
[grunts] big mistake.

21:32.110 --> 21:33.111
Okay.

21:34.029 --> 21:35.322
It's not a mistake.

21:36.198 --> 21:37.324
You're the one for me.

21:41.578 --> 21:43.496
And you can keep the TV.

21:43.580 --> 21:45.040
You can put it in the guest room
or something.

21:45.123 --> 21:47.209
You can watch your <i>Deadliest Ax Man.</i>

21:48.585 --> 21:51.254
That... that ain't a show.

21:51.338 --> 21:53.423
But if it was,
I'd binge watch the shit out of it.

22:03.266 --> 22:04.434
Hey, Joanne.

22:04.517 --> 22:05.768
Hey, Beau.

22:05.853 --> 22:07.395
Smells like something's burning.

22:07.479 --> 22:09.689
Yeah, that must be
your Chevy's transmission.

22:09.772 --> 22:11.358
- [chuckles]
- Come on in.

22:13.651 --> 22:14.987
Can I get you a drink?

22:15.070 --> 22:17.364
Well, I wouldn't mind a glass of wine.

22:17.447 --> 22:19.366
- Whiskey it is.
- [chuckles]

22:23.495 --> 22:26.164
I gotta say, I'm surprised you called.

22:27.165 --> 22:29.292
Truth be told, I misdialed.

22:30.961 --> 22:34.214
Damn Koreans make
those cell phone buttons too small.

22:37.717 --> 22:39.970
You really know how to make
a girl feel special.

22:41.429 --> 22:42.890
Where's Colt and Rooster?

22:42.973 --> 22:44.766
Far away from me as they can get.

22:44.849 --> 22:47.269
- I thought about going there. [Chuckles]
- Yeah.

22:48.811 --> 22:49.938
Why'd they go?

22:51.023 --> 22:53.358
Well, I told them
they could inseminate the herd,

22:53.441 --> 22:55.402
- and then I took it away from 'em.
- Oh.

22:55.485 --> 22:57.654
Now, they won't stop whining about it.

22:58.571 --> 23:00.157
They ought to be grateful.

23:00.240 --> 23:02.575
I've given them more
than anybody ever gave me.

23:02.659 --> 23:03.743
Oh, yeah?

23:05.162 --> 23:07.956
You, uh, buy this ranch yourself, did ya?

23:09.291 --> 23:10.333
All right.

23:11.251 --> 23:13.921
I can probably rustle you up a to-go box.

23:17.340 --> 23:18.883
Did you know I have a daughter?

23:19.592 --> 23:21.428
I don't think you've ever mentioned her.

23:22.845 --> 23:24.847
And if Colt and Rooster are around...

23:25.557 --> 23:27.850
- you should never mention her.
- [chuckles]

23:29.436 --> 23:30.687
When she was in her 20s,

23:30.770 --> 23:33.815
she was dating this guy
who was a real piece of work.

23:33.898 --> 23:36.443
He was in a Meat Loaf cover band.

23:37.402 --> 23:40.072
He was the drummer.
He wasn't even Meat Loaf.

23:42.740 --> 23:45.285
They used to stay out
all hours drinking,

23:45.368 --> 23:47.996
doing God knows what else.

23:48.997 --> 23:50.665
And then, one day,
she threatened to elope.

23:50.748 --> 23:53.543
And I told her that guy
was nothing but trouble

23:53.626 --> 23:55.128
and if she married that deadbeat

23:55.212 --> 23:57.714
she would never be welcome
in my house again.

23:59.132 --> 24:01.468
So she did and she wasn't.

24:03.178 --> 24:05.097
Yeah, sometimes they don't listen.

24:05.180 --> 24:07.975
Three years later,
she divorced his cheating ass.

24:08.933 --> 24:11.478
Who fucks the drummer
in a Meat Loaf cover band?

24:19.152 --> 24:20.237
So, you were right.

24:20.320 --> 24:23.448
Yeah, but our relationship
never recovered.

24:24.949 --> 24:28.620
I crossed a line with her
and she still hasn't forgiven me.

24:29.496 --> 24:30.872
Yeah, that's too bad.

24:31.873 --> 24:34.417
But, still, it's on her.

24:35.043 --> 24:36.461
[sighs]

24:36.544 --> 24:38.380
I also have a granddaughter.

24:39.506 --> 24:40.923
She just turned six.

24:41.883 --> 24:43.301
Her name's Nicole.

24:43.385 --> 24:44.927
Well, that's great.

24:46.888 --> 24:48.098
I've never met her.

24:50.058 --> 24:51.101
So...

24:51.934 --> 24:54.687
sometimes, being right
isn't the most important thing.

24:58.150 --> 24:59.484
I appreciate that.

25:04.072 --> 25:05.698
Thanks, Joanne.

25:05.782 --> 25:07.450
Well, I hope it helps.

25:08.826 --> 25:12.164
'Cause I know,
underneath all that anger and mustache,

25:12.247 --> 25:13.498
there's a heart in there.

25:15.083 --> 25:16.376
That what you think?

25:16.459 --> 25:19.171
Well, you wouldn't have
invited me over if there wasn't.

25:20.505 --> 25:23.091
What can I say? I enjoy your company.

25:23.175 --> 25:25.843
- [chuckles]
- You're welcome here anytime.

25:25.927 --> 25:27.137
Thanks.

25:28.888 --> 25:32.434
Suppose this would be a bad time
to tell you we're having meat loaf.

25:39.191 --> 25:40.650
- I'm just kidding.
- [chuckles]

25:40.733 --> 25:42.110
I'm gonna go put the steaks on.

25:42.194 --> 25:44.404
I like mine with A1 sauce.

25:45.613 --> 25:47.449
- Get out of here.
- [laughs]

25:52.745 --> 25:54.789
[shivers] Hey.

25:54.872 --> 25:57.041
Oh, good. You got my text.

25:58.168 --> 25:59.294
Uh...

26:01.254 --> 26:03.465
Yes. I am not just here to drink.

26:04.382 --> 26:05.425
What's up?

26:05.508 --> 26:06.551
- So, listen...
- [sighs]

26:06.634 --> 26:08.720
I know things have been getting worse
and worse with your dad.

26:08.803 --> 26:11.181
So, I called Ed Bishop.

26:12.724 --> 26:13.766
[Rooster] Okay.

26:13.850 --> 26:15.310
Why do I want to talk to Ed Bishop?

26:15.393 --> 26:18.980
Because he may say
something you want to hear.

26:19.814 --> 26:20.940
- Like what?
- Well...

26:21.023 --> 26:23.776
[sighs] for starters, he'll probably say,
"Drinks are on me."

26:25.320 --> 26:26.529
I'll talk to Ed.

26:28.740 --> 26:31.326
All right, I'll see what he's got to say.

26:31.409 --> 26:32.702
Make it two beers, please.

26:36.623 --> 26:38.333
One of these is for Ed, right?

26:39.751 --> 26:41.253
Uh, three beers, please.

26:43.838 --> 26:45.507
[exhales heavily] Hey, Ed.

26:45.590 --> 26:46.758
Hi, Rooster.

26:47.800 --> 26:49.261
Still screwing them cows?

26:49.344 --> 26:50.720
[chuckles] I thought it was sheep.

26:50.803 --> 26:52.597
[chuckles] So, you admit it.

26:52.680 --> 26:53.931
[chuckles]

26:55.183 --> 26:57.519
[sighing] So... what's new?

26:57.602 --> 27:00.605
Been spending all my time
at the old McConnell ranch.

27:00.688 --> 27:02.732
Some Hollywood dipshit bought it.

27:02.815 --> 27:04.734
Let his eight-year-old rename it.

27:04.817 --> 27:07.154
Now it's... [imitates child]
"My Little Pony Ranch."

27:08.321 --> 27:09.656
[chuckles]

27:09.739 --> 27:12.033
That's pretty badass
for an eight-year-old.

27:12.116 --> 27:14.827
The guy doesn't know
the first thing about ranching.

27:14.911 --> 27:17.705
Called his tractor "the diggin' thingy."

27:17.789 --> 27:18.956
[Rooster laughs]

27:19.416 --> 27:21.918
Must be the same guy
I ran into at the feed shop.

27:22.001 --> 27:23.753
He asked me where the, uh,

27:23.836 --> 27:25.963
closest charging station was
for his Tesla.

27:26.047 --> 27:27.382
[chuckles] What'd you tell him?

27:27.465 --> 27:29.133
- California.
- [chuckles]

27:30.427 --> 27:34.347
Unfortunately, that wannabe cowboy
is my responsibility.

27:34.431 --> 27:36.641
He's overgrazing his land.

27:36.724 --> 27:39.227
And he's not even
cross-checking his breeds.

27:39.311 --> 27:40.812
Hmm.

27:40.895 --> 27:42.855
Well, he's just gotta move
the cows around, you know,

27:42.939 --> 27:45.275
turn the ground over, re-seed it.

27:45.358 --> 27:48.320
Then he should sell some of them heifers
and bring in some new bulls.

27:48.403 --> 27:50.405
See, that's what we need.

27:50.488 --> 27:51.823
Someone like you

27:51.906 --> 27:54.576
who knows what they're talking about.

27:54.659 --> 27:56.494
What do you say to working for us?

27:57.579 --> 27:58.621
You serious?

27:58.705 --> 28:01.791
You're a great rancher, Rooster.
Always have been.

28:01.874 --> 28:03.835
If your daddy can't see it,
that's on him.

28:03.918 --> 28:05.212
We'd love to have you.

28:06.003 --> 28:08.548
The ranch is already staffed up.

28:08.631 --> 28:10.800
You'd be in charge
of the whole operation.

28:13.553 --> 28:14.596
Whoa.

28:14.679 --> 28:18.057
Oh, I'm... I'm not trying
to get in between you and your dad.

28:18.140 --> 28:20.268
I'm sorry if I overstepped my bounds.

28:20.352 --> 28:23.230
No, I...
I wanna keep talking about this.

28:23.313 --> 28:25.398
Let me go grab a couple whiskeys.

28:25.482 --> 28:27.695
You want something, too?

